Updated: 10:39 am

Good Morning, RCSD Families.

We are receiving reports from Otus that the login issue should be resolved.
All students, families, and staff should be able to login.

Otus is still working on resolving the performance issues being reported to development, and are starting to report improvements to functionality.

We apologize for any inconvenience, and appreciate your patience.

Thank you,

The Roseville City School District

****************

Good morning RCSD Families,

Otus is experiencing performance issues, and is currently not accessible to all students, families, and staff.
We have reached out to Otus Support, and they are aware of the issue, and their development team is working swiftly to resolve it.

We know students are waiting to get into their classes and on their Zoom meetings. We will email all RCSD Families an update once it has been fixed and students are able to log on.

We apologize for the inconvenience.

Sincerely,

The Roseville City School District

Dear Roseville City School District Families,

An email went out this morning to all families today regarding the three school options for the 2020-2021 school year. Please click the link to see the details of the email including FAQ documents and the enrollment form:

https://www.rcsdk8.org/article/parent-and-staff-communication-july-9-2020

As a reminder, please complete the following Learning Program Enrollment Forms by July 12th, 2020, to request placement in either the K-8 Hybrid or Champions Academy.

If you would like your child in the traditional five-day a week program you do not need to complete the form, your child will default into this program.

Thank you for your understanding, and we will continue to keep our families updated throughout the summer.

Respectfully,

Derk Garcia
Superintendent

Monday, May 18 is a Staff Development Day. This means there will be no new instruction and all teachers will be "offline."

This day will allow teachers to plan lessons for the remainder of the year and prep curriculum for the 2020-2021 school year.

Need some ideas for keeping your children learning on May 18? Here are some to try:

-independent reading
-catching up on incomplete assignments
-trying a new, no-bake recipe for the family
-creating a chalk "obstacle" course
-writing a letter to a neighbor or friend

We celebrate Teacher Appreciation Week every year, but this year "hits different" (as the kids say).

This year, our teachers have absolutely blown us away with their dedication to student education in the face of immense challenges. Yes, we are proud of how our teachers have been able to bring learning online, but we are more proud of the love, care and genuine concern they demonstrate for each and every one of their students.

Happy Teacher Appreciation Week to our crew of outstanding educators. We love you, we need you and we miss you.

Does your student have a special message to show their appreciation for their teacher? Drop the love below! <3

If your family is in need of meals for your child(ren), we are still disributing meals Monday - Friday at RCSD Woodbridge Elementary, RCSD Cirby Elementary, RCSD Eich Middle School and RCSD Buljan Middle School, 11:00 AM - 12:30 PM. All meals will be served in grab-and-go bags for students to take home.

All meals will be served in grab-and-go bags for students to take home.

post_text:
THE RCSD FACTOR | "Our children attend RCSD Diamond Creek School and RCSD Cooley.

What we love most about our schools are the teachers and staff! Every teacher we have had, as well as principals and vice principals display, a dedication and love for their students like I have never seen. Being a former educator, I know the difference between educators who are ALL IN and who are NOT. Diamond Creek has become an extension of our family. Diamond Creek IS a second home to us! In addition, the administrators, teachers and staff at Cooley have shown incredible dedication to our oldest son, Jack.

One of the main reasons we moved to Roseville in 2012 was because of the schools and their stellar reputation. Because I am most familiar with Diamond Creek, I can tell you honestly it has been one of the greatest assets to our family and confirms our decision to move here!"

post_text:
Siblings Eric Denio and Tracie Denio were born and raised in Roseville, proud alumni of RCSD Cirby and RCSD Eich. If their last name sounds familiar, you're right! Both are third generation Denio's Roseville Farmers Market & Swap Meet leaders in the family business.

Eric served in the U.S. Marine Corps for 8 years with 2 tours of duty in Iraq. A member of Rotary Club of Roseville and graduate of Roseville Area Chamber of Commerce's Leadership Roseville, Eric currently serves as Operations Manager for Denio's Roseville Farmers Market and Swap Meet.

Tracie received her Bachelor of Science degree from Humphreys University and serves on the board of the California Swap Meet Association and DF Properties. Tracie currently serves as General Manager for Denio's Roseville Farmers Market and Swap Meet.

Thank you for your continued patience and understanding as our community takes unprecedented measures in response to help slow the spread of COVID-19. We are aware the closure of schools can bring added stress to families. In an effort to help alleviate a small portion, we have implemented the following to allow Food Services to continue, free of charge, for all children age 18 and under.

**Update**

The Roseville City School District is committed to serving our children nutritious meals during the current school closure. To that end, we continue to serve breakfast from 7:30 - 8:30 and lunches from 11:00 - 12:30 at the following school locations:

Cirby Elementary School
Woodbridge Elementary School
Eich Middle School
Buljan Middle School

Thank you again.

Hello RCSD Families,

All Roseville City School District schools are open. In accordance with Executive Order N-25-20, signed by Governor Newsom last night, we are determining our essential and non-essential functions to slow the community spread of COVID-19. Public education is deemed an essential function by the State of California; however, activities outside of the school day may be considered non-essential.

Effective March 13, we will implement more stringent guidelines, as recommended by the California Department of Public Health. Please see our District website to see the most up-to-date information and details regarding COVID-19.

https://www.rcsdk8.org/district-alert/coronavirus-covid-19-updates

Dear Parents and Guardians,

The online registration process has launched for the 2020-2021 school year!

-How and when do I get started?

Begin the registration process at https://www.rcsdk8.org/student-registration. We‚Äôd like students verified as soon as possible!

All students returning to RCSD will be required to have the online registration process completed to ensure space in our schools for the upcoming school year. Current students advancing from elementary to middle school will register as returning students even though they are going to a new school.

-Can I complete the registration process from my mobile phone or tablet?

Yes! Go to the District website link provided above, and select either the 2020-21 New Student Registration or 2020-21 Returning Student Registration buttons to begin.

Your Partners in Education,
Roseville City School District

post_text:
The Roseville City School District has named Manny Villalpando as principal of the District‚Äôs 20th school, Riego Creek Elementary, located near Pruett Drive and Crawford Parkway off Fiddyment Road in Roseville.

Manny began his career in education in 2001 and became the principal of RCSD Spanger Elementary School in 2017. ‚ÄúMr. Villalpando brings a passion and genuine care to his leadership role and it‚Äôs those characteristics we value in our District culture,‚Äù said Superintendent Derk Garcia. ‚ÄúManny‚Äôs ability to cultivate positive relationships with parents, community members, and staff is an integral piece to our preparation for Riego Creek‚Äôs opening.‚Äù

Construction for Riego Creek was planned for 2022, but due to increased demand, and an agreement with Westpark and Fiddyment Farm developers, the timeline has been expedited so the school can open for the 2020 - 2021 school year and can accommodate up to 625 students.

The next steps include selecting Riego Creek‚Äôs branding, such as mascot, school colors, and logo, as well as the selection of staff. #RCSDChampions

post_text:
RCSD Schools to Remain Open During PG&E Power Shutoff

Good evening RCSD families,

As you may have heard, there is a planned PG&E Public Safety Power Shutoff (PSPS) scheduled for parts of Placer County. The PSPS, which may affect power across Placer County, is beginning October 9th at midnight and may continue for multiple days in some areas.

At this time, it does not appear that any of our schools will be affected. We will have school as normally scheduled for the remainder of the week. Should anything change, we will notify our families immediately.

We will continue to work the utility departments, the City of Roseville, and Placer County to monitor the PSPS bringing you updates should conditions change.

Thank you for your continued support.

Derk Garcia
Superintendent

Do you work in a STEM Field or interested helping with an after-school STEM enrichment class? Come be a STEM Mentor!

Snap the Gap is a non-profit initiative aimed at closing the gender gap in STEM. The mission of Snap the Gap is to instill every 10-12-year-old girl with the courage, confidence, and tools needed to become tomorrow‚Äôs STEM leaders.

We have a program currently at Cirby Elementary school and will have additional programs throughout the year at Woodbridge and Kaseberg. While our meetings are weekly, if you can‚Äôt make a 10-week commitment, we would love to have you join us for a couple of meetings!

If you are interested please contact Donna Sangwin at donna@recreate.org.

The California Positive Behavioral Interventions and Supports (PBIS) Coalition seeks to identify schools that are implementing and sustaining PBIS for their students in their annual state recognition system. The RCSD Board of Education joined the California PBIS Coalition to celebrate and honor six RCSD schools, all earning recognition in 2018-2019.

RCSD Brown, RCSD Eich, and RCSD Woodbridge received the Silver Implementation Award, RCSD Buljan and Blue Oaks Elementary received the Gold Implementation Award, and Robert C. Cooley Middle received the highest honor of the Platinum Implementation Award! Congrats to all of these schools on their recognition. #rcsdchampions
